===WNIT results=== Kansas State has appeared in the [[Women's National Invitation Tournament]] five times, including the first tournament held, in 1969.<ref name=history/> The school was also invited to the tournament in 1970, 1999, 2006 and 2007. Kansas State won the tournament in 2006 and reached the semifinals again in 2007.
